---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Is OX a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Plus Best OX Plays)"
  description="OX is a valid Scrabble word worth 9 points. Learn the best OX plays on premium squares, words containing OX, and how to use OX as a parallel play enabler."
  keywords="is ox a scrabble word, ox scrabble, ox scrabble word, ox points scrabble, two letter words with x, ox valid scrabble, words with ox"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Is OX a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Plus Best OX Plays)",
    "description": "OX is a valid Scrabble word worth 9 points. Learn the best OX plays on premium squares and words containing OX.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-23",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-ox-a-scrabble-word" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is OX a valid Scrabble word?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, OX is valid in both the TWL (North American) and SOWPODS (International) Scrabble dictionaries. It scores 9 points (O=1, X=8) and is one of only five 2-letter words containing the X tile." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What words contain OX in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Common words containing OX include OXEN (11pts), OXIDE (13pts), FOXED (16pts), BOXER (14pts), OXBOW (17pts), TOXIC (14pts), and PROXY (17pts). OX also hooks to form OXO, OXY, and OXES." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many points is OX worth in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "OX scores 9 points in Scrabble (O=1, X=8). On a Double Word square, OX scores 18 points. With X on a Triple Letter square, OX scores 25 points. OX is tied with AX, EX, XI, and XU as the highest-scoring 2-letter X words." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/strategy/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Strategy</a>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is OX a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Plus Best OX Plays)</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-23">June 23, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Yes, OX is a valid Scrabble word. It scores 9 points and is accepted in both TWL (North American) and SOWPODS (International) dictionaries. OX means a domesticated bovine animal, and it is one of the most useful 2-letter X words because it enables powerful parallel plays and hooks into longer words like OXEN, OXIDE, and FOXED.
      </p>

      <!-- Hero Card -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">✓ Valid</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">OX</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">9 points · Valid TWL + SOWPODS · A domesticated bovine</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">OX is one of five 2-letter X words in Scrabble. It pairs the common O tile with the 8-point X tile for a quick 9-point play that works brilliantly on premium squares and as a parallel play enabler.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Stat Strip -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">TWL+SOWPODS</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Dictionary</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letters</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">How to Use OX in Scrabble</h2>

      <p>OX shines as a parallel play enabler. Because O is one of the most common letters on the board, you can almost always find a spot to slide OX next to an existing word, scoring in two directions at once.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel plays:</span> Place OX adjacent to existing words where O and X each form valid crosswords. OX beside a word ending in I creates XI downward — a valid word worth bonus points in both directions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Premium square targeting:</span> X on a Triple Letter square turns OX into a 25-point play. On a Double Word square, OX scores 18 points. Always scan for TL squares near an existing O on the board.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hook into longer words:</span> OX extends to OXEN, OXES, OXO, and OXY. If OX is already on the board, adding EN to make OXEN scores extra points by building on your previous play.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Words Containing OX</h2>

      <p>Knowing words with OX inside them lets you build longer plays and set up future moves.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">OX- Words (starts with OX)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">OXEN (11pts) · OXES (11pts) · OXIDE (13pts) · OXBOW (17pts) · OXO (10pts) · OXY (13pts)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">-OX- Words (contains OX)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">FOXED (16pts) · BOXER (14pts) · TOXIC (14pts) · PROXY (17pts) · EPOXY (17pts) · FOXES (15pts)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Premium Square Scoring</h2>

      <p>OX becomes explosive on premium squares. Here is what OX scores in different positions:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Base Score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">X on DL</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">25</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">X on TL</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">OX on DW</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/all-2-letter-scrabble-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">All 2-Letter Scrabble Words: Complete List for 2026</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-cheat-sheet/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Cheat Sheet: Essential Words & Strategy</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/best-x-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best X Words in Scrabble: High-Scoring Plays</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find more X words instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
